Days like today are a welcome sight to the savvy investor who was rebalancing overweight positions into the end of the year and executing a game plan to act on local price weakness. Nobody made money running from a sale. The only thing that changed today was price. The earnings trajectory didn't change, the economic outlook didn't change, just price. Price generally gets adjusted to reflect the value of the equity risk premium. It's why the average 3m gain for the SPX after the first rate hike is just .3%. There is usually some pricing in ahead and through, but a catch up thereafter to reflect an almost flat market post first rate hike.  
 
You're either following the data or flailing about, chasing and reacting without a plan! Be savvy  mate ;-)
